2. Leak Exception
In the event that the source code is leaked or made publicly available through unofficial channels, the prohibition on modifications is temporarily waived for the purpose of security research and critical bug fixes. However:

You must notify the original authors immediately at babyyodacutefry@gmail.com with details of the leak.

You must collaborate to reinstate the official version.

After the leak is resolved, you must cease any further modifications and revert to the official unmodified code.

This exception exists solely to protect users from malicious code that may be injected during a leak. It is not a loophole for permanent forks.

