Failure to provide proper attribution will be considered a violation of this license.

5. Takedown Policy
We actively monitor public instances of the Software. If we discover any public instance that has been modified without authorization:

We will politely request that the instance be taken down or that the modifications be removed.

You will have 7 days to comply.

If the request is not honored, we reserve the right to take further legal action, including but not limited to DMCA takedown notices and cease‑and‑desist letters.

We believe in open communication and will always attempt to resolve issues amicably first. However, persistent violations will be met with appropriate legal measures.

